\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \cf0 \expnd0\expndtw0\kerning0
\outl0\strokewidth0 \strokec2 # KB-7 Complete Synchronization Architecture: Dual-Stream Implementation
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Executive Summary
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 This document provides the complete implementation of the dual-stream synchronization architecture, addressing the critical distinction between real-time patient data flow and near-real-time knowledge synchronization, with full details on the Adapter Layer, CDC implementation, and insight distribution patterns.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## 1. Dual-Stream Architecture Overview
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```mermaid
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 graph TB
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0subgraph "Stream 1: Patient Data (Real-Time)"
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0EHR[EHR Events] --> |sub-second| Harmonizer
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 \'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0\'a0Harmonizer --> |<100ms| Kafka1[Patient Events Kafka]
