\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Critical Architecture Completions
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 1. **Dual-Stream Separation**
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 The implementation clearly distinguishes between:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Patient Data Stream**: Sub-second latency through direct Kafka streaming
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Knowledge Sync Stream**: 1-4 second latency using CDC (Debezium) for KB changes
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 The Debezium configuration captures changes from GraphDB's underlying PostgreSQL storage, providing reliable change data capture without modifying the authoritative KBs.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 2. **Multi-KB Integration in Semantic Mesh**
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 The adapter correctly pulls from multiple KBs:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - KB-7 provides terminology (the "nouns")
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - KB-4 provides safety rules (the "verbs" and relationships)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - KB-2 provides clinical context
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 This is implemented in the `AdapterTransformer` class with specific handlers for each KB type.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 3. **Flink Output Distribution**
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 The multi-sink pattern ensures insights reach all necessary systems:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **FHIR Store** (system of record) - permanent storage
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Elasticsearch** (system of retrieval) - searchable index
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Firebase** (system of engagement) - immediate notifications
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Neo4j** (optional lightweight summary) - graph queries
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Each sink has different guarantees and optimizations appropriate to its use case.
\f1\fs24 \
\

