\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Key Technical Decisions Validated
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Why Debezium for CDC?
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - No modification needed to source systems
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Guaranteed delivery with Kafka backing
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Handles schema evolution gracefully
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Battle-tested in production environments
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Why Separate Transformation Service?
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Decouples RDF/OWL complexity from runtime stores
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Allows independent scaling of transformation logic
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Provides clear audit trail of all transformations
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Enables replay of changes if needed
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Why Multiple Sinks for Insights?
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Different systems optimize for different access patterns
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - FHIR for compliance and interoperability
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Elasticsearch for full-text search
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Push notifications for urgency
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Allows independent scaling and maintenance
\f1\fs24 \
\

